<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="surprising-adj">surprising <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sə'praɪzɪŋ/    美 /sər'praɪzɪŋ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>令人吃惊的；惊人的；出人意料的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We had a surprising amount in common. 
我们的共同之处出奇得多。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It’s not surprising that</strong> the cheap machine broke down only a week later. 
这部廉价的机器一周后就坏了，一点也不奇怪。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>surprisingly /sə'praɪzɪŋli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It seems that living green is <strong><em>_</em></strong> (surprising) easy and affordable. A small step makes a big difference.
  （2009 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. surprisingly  </p></div>